verses.verse: Let my supplication come before You; Deliver me according to Your word.
(Ps. 119:27, 144) My lips shall utter praise, For You teach me Your statutes.
My tongue shall speak of Your word, For all Your commandments are righteousness.
Let Your hand become my help, For (Ps. 119:7) I have chosen Your precepts.
(Josh. 24:22; Luke 10:42) I long for Your salvation, O LORD, And (Ps. 119:166) Your law is my delight.
Let my soul live, and it shall praise You; And let Your judgments help me.
(Ps. 119:16, 24) I have gone astray like a lost sheep; Seek Your servant, For I do not forget Your commandments.
(Plea for Relief from Bitter Foes) A Song of Ascents. [1] In ((Is. 53:6); Jer. 50:6; Matt. 18:12; Luke 15:4; (1 Pet. 2:25)) my distress I cried to the LORD, And He heard me.
